  "prompt": "Do ants have feelings?",
  "response": "Ants do not have feelings in the way humans do. They lack the complex nervous systems and brain structures that are associated with emotions in mammals. While ants do exhibit behaviors like teamwork, communication, and problem-solving, these are driven by instinct and chemical signaling rather than emotions. Ants operate based on programmed behaviors and simple responses to environmental stimuli, which are not linked to any conscious emotional experience.",
